\subsection{\href{https://beta.lmfdb.org/knowledge/show/lf.family_diagrams}{$p$-adic field family diagrams}}
\begin{definition}\label{lf.family_diagrams}
\uses{lf.eisenstein_diagram,lf.family_polynomial,lf.herbrand_function,lf.means,lf.ramification_polygon,lf.rams,lf.slopes}
\leanok
There are three diagrams that are helpful for visualizing a \hyperref[lf.family_polynomial]{$p$-adic family} with wild ramification:

\begin{itemize}
\item  The \hyperref[lf.eisenstein_diagram]{Eisenstein diagram}, which explains the construction of the defining polynomial of the family.
\item  The \hyperref[lf.ramification_polygon]{ramification polygon}, whose slopes are the \hyperref[lf.rams]{rams} of every extension in the family.
\item  The graph of the \hyperref[lf.herbrand_function]{Herbrand function}
\end{itemize}
of the family, which helps clarify the relationship between
\hyperref[lf.slopes]{slopes}, \hyperref[lf.rams]{rams} and
\hyperref[lf.means]{means}.
\end{definition}


